> This is the only source of truth for the database design.

---

## Role Structure (V1 — 2 Tiers Only)

```
SUPER_ADMIN (platform owner)
      │
      ▼
ADMIN (business clients — each manages their own leads)
```

- `CLIENT` exists as an enum value only — reserved for V2. No tables, routes, or UI reference it in V1.
- Leads belong directly to an **ADMIN**, not to a CLIENT under an ADMIN.
- Each ADMIN has their own WhatsApp Business number and credentials stored in `AdminSettings`.

---

## Tables

### 1. User

All platform users. In V1 only SUPER_ADMIN and ADMIN are active roles.

| Field | Type | Notes |
|-------|------|-------|
| `id` | String (UUID) | PK |
| `email` | String | Unique |
| `password` | String | bcrypt hashed, cost ≥ 12. Never plaintext. |
| `name` | String | Display name |
| `role` | Enum (UserRole) | SUPER_ADMIN or ADMIN in V1 |
| `status` | Enum (UserStatus) | ACTIVE / SUSPENDED / DELETED |
| `createdAt` | DateTime | Auto |
| `updatedAt` | DateTime | Auto |
| `lastLoginAt` | DateTime? | Updated on successful login |

**Indexes**: `role`, `status`

**Relations**: `leads`, `activities`, `followUps`, `settings` (→ AdminSettings)

**No `adminId` field** — there is no parent-child User relationship in V1. ADMIN accounts are created directly by SUPER_ADMIN.

#### Access by Role

| Operation | SUPER_ADMIN | ADMIN |
|-----------|:-----------:|:-----:|
| Read all users | ✅ | ❌ |
| Read own profile | ✅ | ✅ |
| Create ADMIN accounts | ✅ | ❌ |
| Edit any user | ✅ | ❌ |
| Edit own profile | ✅ | ✅ |
| Suspend/delete any user | ✅ | ❌ |
| See `password` field | ❌ | ❌ |

