### 2. AdminSettings

Per-admin configuration. **Each ADMIN has exactly one row.**
WhatsApp and email credentials are stored here, not in SystemSettings.
`whatsappToken`, `whatsappWebhookSecret`, and `smtpPass` are **AES-256 encrypted** before storage.

| Field | Type | Notes |
|-------|------|-------|
| `id` | String (UUID) | PK |
| `adminId` | String (FK → User.id) | Unique — one settings row per admin |
| `whatsappToken` | String? | AES-256 encrypted |
| `whatsappPhoneNumberId` | String? | Meta Business phone number ID |
| `whatsappWebhookSecret` | String? | AES-256 encrypted |
| `smtpHost` | String? | Email server |
| `smtpPort` | Int? | Email port |
| `smtpUser` | String? | Email username |
| `smtpPass` | String? | AES-256 encrypted |
| `emailFrom` | String? | Sender address |
| `timezone` | String | Default: "Asia/Kolkata" |
| `reminderLeadTime` | Int | Minutes before follow-up to fire reminder. Default: 30 |
| `updatedAt` | DateTime | Auto |

**Cascade**: deleted when parent User is deleted.

#### Access by Role

| Operation | SUPER_ADMIN | ADMIN |
|-----------|:-----------:|:-----:|
| Read any admin's settings | ✅ | ❌ |
| Read own settings | ✅ | ✅ |
| Write any admin's settings | ✅ | ❌ |
| Write own settings | ❌ | ✅ |

> SUPER_ADMIN can read all settings (for support/debugging) but writing is the ADMIN's responsibility. SUPER_ADMIN can override in exceptional cases.

